doc.after: Jamtlandic or Jamtish jamska jamsk formally a definite form in Jamtlandic is a well defined group of dialects of Scandinavia It is spoken in the Swedish province of J mtland It is commonly used in the region between the modern Swedish Norwegian border in the west and the pre 1645 Swedish Norwegian border in the east though Tr ndersk is spoken in Frostviken in the northernmost part of J mtland colonized in the 18th century by Norwegians and Norrlandic is spoken in Ragunda in the easternmost part of J mtland which until the 13th century was a part of ngermanland
